B048C004V000	48	4	0	Breaking with the Truth of the Gospel means a Return to the Demiurge and his Angelic and Elementary Principles
B048C004V003	48	4	3	
        
B048C004V004	48	4	4	But when the fullness of time had come, God sent forth his Son, born of woman, 
B048C004V005	48	4	5	to redeem those who were under the law, so that we might receive adoption as sons.
B048C004V006	48	4	6	And because 
B048C004V007	48	4	7	
        
B048C004V008	48	4	8	
        
B048C004V009	48	4	9	But now that you have come to know God, or rather to be known by God, how can you turn back again to the weak and worthless elementary principles of the world [that are, according to marcionite-gnostic doctrine, responsible for the law] whose slaves you want to be once more?
B048C004V010	48	4	10	You observe days and months and seasons and years 
B048C004V011	48	4	11	I am afraid I may have labored over you in vain.
B048C004V000	48	4	0	Personal Address: from God’s Angel to “Enemy”
B048C004V012	48	4	12	Brothers, I entreat you, become as I am, for I also have become as you are. You did me no wrong.
B048C004V013	48	4	13	You know it was because of a bodily ailment that I preached the gospel to you at first,
B048C004V014	48	4	14	and though my condition was a trial to you, you did not scorn or despise me, but received me as an angel of God, as Christ Jesus.
B048C004V015	48	4	15	What then has become of the blessing you felt? For I testify to you that, if possible, you would have gouged out your eyes and given them to me.
B048C004V016	48	4	16	Have I then become your enemy by telling you the truth [of the Gospel]?
B048C004V017	48	4	17	They make much of you, but for no good purpose. They want to shut you out, that you may make much of them.
B048C004V018	48	4	18	It is always good to be made much of for a good purpose, and not only when I am present with you,
B048C004V019	48	4	19	my little children, for whom I am again in the anguish of childbirth until Christ is formed in you!
B048C004V020	48	4	20	I wish I could be present with you now and change my tone, for I am perplexed about you.
B048C004V000	48	4	0	Allegorical Exegesis: the Faithful as Sons of the Free Woman, not of the Slave
B048C004V021	48	4	21	Tell me, you who desire to be under the law, do you not listen to the law?
B048C004V022	48	4	22	For it is written that Abraham had two sons, one by a slave woman and one by a free woman.
B048C004V023	48	4	23	But the son of the slave was born according to the flesh, while the son of the free woman was born through promise. (30)
B048C004V024	48	4	24	Now this may be interpreted allegorically: these women are two covenants. One is from Mount Sinai, bearing children 
