B048C004V030	48	4	30	
        
B048C004V031	48	4	31	So, brothers, we are not children of the slave but of the free woman.
B048C005V000	48	5	0	If a man accepts  Circumcision he does no   longer belong to Christ but acts against the Truth of the Gospel
B048C005V001	48	5	1	
        
B048C005V002	48	5	2	Look: I, Paul, say to you that if you accept circumcision, Christ will be of no advantage to you.
B048C005V003	48	5	3	I testify again 
B048C005V004	48	5	4	
        
B048C005V005	48	5	5	For through the Spirit, by faith, we ourselves eagerly wait for the hope of righteousness.
B048C005V006	48	5	6	
        
B048C005V007	48	5	7	You were running well. Who hindered you from obeying the truth?
B048C005V008	48	5	8	This persuasion is not from him who calls you.
B048C005V009	48	5	9	A little leaven 
B048C005V010	48	5	10	I have confidence 
B048C005V011	48	5	11	But if I, brothers, still preach circumcision, why am I still being persecuted? In that case the offense of the cross has been removed.
B048C005V012	48	5	12	I wish those who unsettle you would emasculate themselves!
B048C005V013	48	5	13	For you were called to freedom, brothers. Only do not use your freedom as an opportunity for the flesh, but through love serve one another.
B048C005V014	48	5	14	For the whole law is fulfilled for you 
B048C005V015	48	5	15	But if you bite and devour one another, watch out that you are not consumed by one another.
B048C005V000	48	5	0	  The Flesh Crucified: Walking by the Spirit, not by the Flesh
B048C005V016	48	5	16	But I say, walk by the Spirit, and you will not gratify the desires of the flesh.
B048C005V017	48	5	17	For the desires of the flesh are against the Spirit, and the desires of the Spirit are against the flesh, for these are opposed to each other, to keep you from doing the things you want to do.
B048C005V018	48	5	18	But if you are led by the Spirit, you are not under the law.
B048C005V019	48	5	19	Now the works of the flesh are evident: [adultery] sexual immorality, impurity, sensuality,
B048C005V020	48	5	20	idolatry, sorcery, enmity, strife, jealousy, fits of anger, rivalries, dissensions, divisions,
B048C005V021	48	5	21	
        
B048C005V022	48	5	22	But the fruit of the Spirit is love, joy, peace, patience, kindness, goodness, faithfulness,
B048C005V023	48	5	23	gentleness, self-control; against such things there is no law.
B048C005V024	48	5	24	And those who belong to Christ 
B048C005V025	48	5	25	If we live by the Spirit, let us also walk by the Spirit.
B048C005V026	48	5	26	Let us not become conceited, provoking one another, envying one another.
B048C006V000	48	6	0	 Conclusions to be Practiced in the Community
B048C006V001	48	6	1	Brothers, if anyone is caught in any transgression, you who are spiritual should restore him in a spirit of gentleness. Keep watch on yourself, lest you too be tempted.
B048C006V002	48	6	2	Bear one another's burdens, and so fulfill the law of Christ.
B048C006V003	48	6	3	For if anyone thinks he is something, when he is nothing, he deceives himself.
B048C006V004	48	6	4	But let each one test his own work, and then his reason to boast will be in himself alone and not in his neighbor.
B048C006V005	48	6	5	For each will have to bear his own load.
B048C006V006	48	6	6	One who is taught the word must share all good things with the one who teaches [him]. (38)
B048C006V007	48	6	7	
        
B048C006V008	48	6	8	For the one who sows to his own flesh will from the flesh reap corruption, but the one who sows to the Spirit will from the Spirit reap eternal life.
B048C006V009	48	6	9	And let us not grow weary of doing good, 
B048C006V010	48	6	10	
        
B048C006V000	48	6	0	The true Motives of the Judaising Heretics
B048C006V011	48	6	11	See with what large letters I am writing to you with my own hand.
B048C006V012	48	6	12	It is those who want to make a good showing in the flesh who would force you to be circumcised, and only in order that they may not be persecuted for the cross of Christ.
B048C006V013	48	6	13	For even those who are circumcised do not themselves keep the law, but they desire to have you circumcised that they may boast in your flesh. (41)
B048C006V014	48	6	14	But far be it from me to boast except in the cross of our Lord Jesus Christ, by which the world has been crucified to me, and I to the world.
B048C006V015	48	6	15	
        
B048C006V016	48	6	16	
        
